Amogelang Sema was last seen playing with a group of children at the Tladi Park on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG An eight-year-old boy who disappeared from a park in Soweto on Tuesday has been found safe. Amogelang Sema was last seen playing with a group of children at the Tladi Park on Tuesday. His frantic mother, Johanna Sema, says she received a call at around midday on Wednesday informing her that her son was at the Meadowlands police station. Sema says she is thankful to the media, the police and all those who helped in the search for the young boy. LISTEN: A child goes missing every five hours in South Africa